args: O power universal...\nBottomless font and blessing of nature...
Hey, it's Xuan Zang and Wu Kong!\nWhat is UP, my dudes?
Greetings, Notte. We are currently\nengaged in sealer training.
Does that training involve Wu Kong\nstraining and grunting like a crazy\nperson? Because if so, he's killing it.
Do you see the pot at his feet?
That is a Qilin relic we call the Yong Run\nHu. It is a pot from which issues forth an\nunceasing flow of water.
Is it busted? 'Cause it's bone dry.
The point of this exercise is to restrain\nthe flow so the water builds up inside\nthe pot, but never spills forth.
In this way, Wu Kong can learn how to\neffectively regulate a Qilin relic.
I understand, like, maybe fifteen percent\nof what you just said—I'm just gonna\nassume it's really hard and leave it at that.

It is indeed a challenge—as is controlling
the power of any Qilin relic. However,
achieving such control is essential to
becoming a sealer.
If one can fill the pot to the brim without\nany water spilling over, it is a sign of\ntheir expert control.
Nnnngh.... There! Done!\nPretty great, eh, master?
You have accomplished your task\nwith aplomb, Wu Kong.
Ha! I couldn't very well call myself the\nsuccessor to Xuan Zang if I couldn't do\nsomething as simple as this!
Boy, you really know how to take a\ncompliment and run with it.

Look, here's the deal: I'm gonna become
just as good a sealer as she is, and then
I'm gonna travel the land taking out every
single Qilin relic I can find!
I wouldn't say troubled, per se.
But SOMETHING is on your mind.
Heh. It seems my emotional control\nis no match for your keen eye.
In truth, I've concerns about Wu Kong.
Oh? He seems like he's been pretty\ndedicated to things lately.
Oh, he is ever the passionate pupil,\nbut since we came to your castle,\nhe has become much more diligent.
As he can take his time and not rush in\ntraining now, the time I can spend\nguiding him has also increased.
Which means his passion has\nnaturally been increasing too.
Just so. Which, I fear, is the problem.
Because Wu Kong so respects me,\nhe has no intention of surpassing me.
Ah, right. He DID mention he wanted to\nbe just like you—for better or for worse.
I confess it fills me with joy to have\na pupil that respects me so.
But it is not good for him to see me and\nmy achievements as the ultimate endpoint\nfor his own works.
If that does not change, I will only become\na hindrance to his future growth.
I guess it might be good for him to\nlearn from other people, in that case.
I had the same thought—which is why I\nwant him to call upon another sealer\nand train with that person instead.
He's going to miss you quite a bit,\nbut I see the wisdom in your plan.
If only his feelings ended at ＂missing me.＂
No, my fear is that he will see this plan\nnot as a step in his growth, but as me\nabandoning him utterly.
This shames me greatly as a teacher.\nI know what is needed for my pupil's\ngrowth, yet emotion stays my hand.
It's a difficult situation for sure.
What are you doing, Wu Kong?\nWe must begin today's training.
I need to talk to you, master.
...I want to study under another sealer.
If I stay with you, I'm never going to grow\ninto a better sealer than you are.
...Did you overhear my discussion with\n{player_name} yesterday?
Huh? No, I don't know anything about that.\nThis is just something I've been thinking\nabout for a while now.
Well, it delights me to hear you say this.
But are you sure you truly feel this way,\nfrom the bottom of your heart? Are you\nhonestly convinced you are in the right?
If you have even the slightest concern—
No matter who I'm training under,\nyou'll always be my teacher!
You truly ARE my finest student.
You will always be my pupil, and as such,\nI will always be your teacher.
I'm going now. With any luck, the next\ntime we meet I will be a sealer the\nlikes of which you've never seen!
And when that time comes, I shall teach\nyou a thing or two about just how\nmagnificent your master is.
Bye, everyone! Until we meet again!
Students grow up so very fast.
Which is a good reminder for me to do\nmy own distancing in the meantime.
